text: Eunidia scotti is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1939.BioLib.cz - Eunidia scotti. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It's 8.5 mm long and 2.25 mm wide, and its type locality is Dire Dawa, Ethiopia. It was named in honor of Hugh Scott. ==References== Category:Eunidiini Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Eunidia scotti
